@page "/docs/extensions/datagrid/grouping"

<Seo Canonical="/docs/extensions/datagrid/grouping" Title="Blazorise DataGrid Grouping" Description="Learn to use and control grouping with the Blazorise DataGrid APIs, to control how and when grouping will be applied." />

<DocsPageTitle>
    DataGrid: Grouping
</DocsPageTitle>

<DocsPageSection>
    <DocsPageSectionHeader Title="Grouping">
        By enabling <Code>Groupable</Code> the DataGrid is able to group your data by page. One of the ways to group data is by providing a custom Function to the DataGrid.
    </DocsPageSectionHeader>
    <DocsPageSectionContent>
        <DataGridGroupingExample />
    </DocsPageSectionContent>
    <DocsPageSectionSource Code="DataGridGroupingExample" />
</DocsPageSection>

<DocsPageSection>
    <DocsPageSectionHeader Title="Single or Multiple Column Grouping">
        You may also provide group by one or more columns by enabling both the column <Code>Groupable</Code>(column can be grouped) && <Code>Grouping</Code>(column should be grouped) Parameters. By default grouping occurs on the column <Code>Field</Code>.
        However you may also provide a custom group Function.
    </DocsPageSectionHeader>
    <DocsPageSectionContent>
        <DataGridMultipleGroupingExample />
    </DocsPageSectionContent>
    <DocsPageSectionSource Code="DataGridMultipleGroupingExample" />
</DocsPageSection>

<DocsPageSection>
    <DocsPageSectionHeader Title="Draggable Column Grouping">
        If the DataGrid's <Code>ShowGrouping</Code> Parameter is enabled, the user may drag & drop columns to be grouped. (Columns should be eligible for grouping by enabling <Code>Groupable</Code>)
    </DocsPageSectionHeader>
    <DocsPageSectionContent>
        <DataGridShowGroupingExample />
    </DocsPageSectionContent>
    <DocsPageSectionSource Code="DataGridShowGroupingExample" />
</DocsPageSection>